			<div class="content" id="post-content-4407988">
									

<p>I was really enjoying this right up until the ending which kinda, botched the landing for me :(</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;longer&nbsp;form&nbsp;thought&nbsp;on&nbsp;this</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;longer&nbsp;form&nbsp;thought</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;I mean come on, Santa Claus? That's just ridiculous.&quot;</p>
<p>The smile quickly slipped off of Ten's face. &quot;Wait, what?&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>There's two ways of reading this: either they were only joking about Santa Claus and everything else is true; or they think that Ten should've realised at Santa Claus and everything else is false. Leaving it ambiguous like this feels, kinda unsatisfying to me and idk, I just, didn't appreciate it.</p>
<p>I'd probably suggest ending it either after the &quot;Wow. Can't believe I actually fell for that.&quot; or the &quot;Thanks, it's good to be here&quot; if you want to change it (or being more explicit about how much was just a joke) but judging from the rating, it might just be me that objects here.</p>
</div>
